<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes — memcpy can access beyond the referenced objects if the size computations underflow or the invariants are not preserved. For example, if pp->buffer_pos > pp->buffer_size then (pp->buffer_size - pp->buffer_pos) underflows (size_t wraparound) producing a very large max and memcpy(&buf[pp->buffer_pos], &post_data[poff], max) will write far past the end of buf. Similarly, if poff > post_data_len then (post_data_len - poff) underflows and max may be large, causing reads beyond post_data. The call is safe only if the invariants pp->buffer_pos <= pp->buffer_size and poff <= post_data_len always hold; otherwise Rule 21.17 is violated.
</scenario>

